para_trans: On extension of temporary posts on Sanjay Gandhi Nirbhaya Subsidy Scheme and other Special Assistance Scheme Establishments.
Department of Social Justice and Fears Aid
Government Decision No: Sangayo 2012 / Q. No.51 / Visayo
Mantralaya Extension Building, Madame Cama Marg,
Read: - 1. Government Decision Finance Department No.: Post-2016 / Q. 8/16 APC, D. 21/02/2024.
Government Decision Social Justice and Special Assistance No: Sangayo 2012 / Q. No.41 / Visayo Dated

Government Decision: - The Government hereby approves the continuation of a total of 1422 temporary posts from the date 01/03/2024 to the date 31/08/2024 subject to the condition that none of the temporary posts on the establishment of the Collector of 35 districts in the accompanying return for implementation of the Sanjay Gandhi Nirbhadra Grants-in-aid Scheme and other special assistance scheme is lying vacant for more than six months. A district-wise report is attached.

The expenditure for this matter shall be met from the provision approved for that financial year under the head Demand No. N-2, Head of Accounts-2053, District Administration (093) District Establishment (01) General Establishment.
3. The Hajasan Decision is being issued in accordance with the authorities received by the Administrative Division under the Government Decision with respect to the Finance Department.
The decision is available on the Government of Maharashtra's Wwww.maharashtra.gov.in website.
